[The newswire above reports that the outbreak of dengue continues to rise in Malaysia. The number of reported dengue cases in 2014 is about 4 times higher than in the same period of 2013.

A map of Malaysia can be seen at http://www.ezilon.com/maps/images/asia/Malaysia-physical-map.gif. For the interactive HealthMap/ProMED-mail map with direct links to other outbreaks in Malaysia and surrounding countries reported on ProMED-mail and PRO/MBDS, see https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2390179,13000. - Mod.QCN]

[A 6 Apr 2014 report in the New Straits Times quoted the minister of health saying that there have been 63 dengue deaths since January 2014. However, the number of new dengue cases is decreasing currently (http://www.nst.com.my/latest/dengue-cases-down-to-1-300-last-week-subramaniam-1.553408). - Mod.TY]

